result.execSummary:
The defendant Shamaul B Pitts was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Disorderly Conduct [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse], a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Defendant Shamaul B Pitts in court.  Patrick D. Winter appeared for the State of Wisconsin.Probation Memorandum received and filed.  Probation agent present in court.  Based upon the defendant's compliance with the conditions of probation, the Court ordered the time in the House of Correction, previously ordered and STAYED  for review on today's date, be STAYED until the termination of probation or for future use at the agent's discretion.

Defendant Shamaul B Pitts in court PRO SE.  Benjamin Calvin Verhulst appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Probation Agent is in court.  Probation Status Review report filed and reviewed.  Defendant is somewhat compliant with probation.  The remaining condition time is stayed.  Court found that further review is needed.  Probation Review Hearing scheduled for October 9, 2015 at 01:30 pm.

Defendant Shamaul B Pitts in court with attorney Frederick F Klimetz.  Defendant Shamaul B Pitts in custody.  Kristin M. Schrank appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  
Pursuant to plea negotiations, on the Motion of the State, Court ordered COUNTS #1, #2 and #4, dismissed and read-in for the purposes of sentencing.

AS TO COUNT #3: Defendant was advised of constitutional rights and maximum penalties, waived all rights, and plead GUILTY.  Defendant examined as to the plea.  Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights and Addendum received and filed.  Stipulation by parties to the Criminal Complaint as a factual basis to sustain the plea.  Court found the defendant guilty as charged in the Information/Complaint. Judgment of conviction entered.  The Court finds that the State has complied with victim notification.  Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.  Additional statements by: Bonnie Adams and Katrice Adams. 

Defendant sentenced to serve 2 MONTHS (CONSECUTIVE to any other sentences), in the House of Correction with credit for 0 days time served.  COURT STAYED THE SENTENCE and placed the defendant on probation with the State of Wisconsin, Department of Corrections for a period of 18 MONTHS.  

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:
* Court ordered the defendant to serve 50 DAYS
   in the House of Correction.  Stayed pending review.
* Successfully complete "Batterers intervention"
   counseling and continue programming.
* Attend and complete parenting classes.
* Defendant to participate in Alcohol and Drug Assessment
   and successfully complete recommended treatment.
* Random urine screens and breathalyzer test.
* Maintain absolute sobriety.  No drugs.  No alcohol.
* Successfully complete any other counseling and/or
   treatment deemed appropriate.
* No violent contact with victim, Tiffany K., 
   parties may not reside together unless approved by agent.      
* Obtain GED/HSED.
* Obtain and maintain employment and/or job training. 
* No firearms; weapons.
* Defendant to pay all applicable costs and surcharges,
   victim/witness surcharge, the domestic violence
   surcharge, DNA surcharge and supervision fees as 
   determined by the Department of Corrections, 
   during period of probation or CIVIL JUDGMENT.
* Restitution is set at zero.
